WEBVTT

00:17.500 --> 00:20.820
It was the month of June and the weather was

00:20.820 --> 00:25.560
beautiful. Stuart left school. He was on

00:25.560 --> 00:29.200
holiday, but he was not happy. He did not have

00:29.200 --> 00:33.220
a motorbike. Stuart was 17 years old.

00:34.140 --> 00:38.920
He left school, but he did not start work. All

00:38.920 --> 00:41.580
his mates started work immediately, but

00:41.580 --> 00:44.700
Stuart did not want to work. He wanted a long

00:44.700 --> 00:54.880
holiday, and he needed a motorbike. Stuart

00:54.880 --> 00:57.440
went to the city full of offices, shops, and factories.

00:58.200 --> 00:59.720
It is not a good place for a

00:59.720 --> 01:04.580
holiday. Martin, a friend of Stuart's, worked in a garage.

01:05.740 --> 01:08.360
Martin had a bike for sale. It

01:08.360 --> 01:14.540
was a beauty, a Japanese Suzuki. Martin wanted 350 pounds

01:14.540 --> 01:16.720
for the bike, but Stuart did not

01:16.720 --> 01:22.220
have 350 pounds. He did not have any money. Stuart

01:22.220 --> 01:24.320
went and looked at the bike every day.

01:24.320 --> 01:30.320
It was a beauty. He wanted to buy it. Where

01:30.320 --> 01:34.880
can I find 350 pounds? Stuart asked himself.

01:36.960 --> 01:41.180
Stuart left the garage and walked back home. His house

01:41.180 --> 01:43.020
was in Blenham Street near the

01:43.020 --> 01:46.920
University. There were lots of old empty houses in Blenham

01:46.920 --> 01:54.300
Street. The University was one of

01:54.300 --> 01:57.780
the land and buildings. Most of the old houses in

01:57.780 --> 01:59.400
Blenham Street belonged to the University.

02:01.180 --> 02:05.320
Some of these houses had been empty for years. Stuart

02:05.320 --> 02:08.120
often searched through them. Sometimes

02:08.120 --> 02:13.500
he found old books and gramophone records. One day, he

02:13.500 --> 02:15.620
told himself, I'll find something

02:15.620 --> 02:20.760
valuable. There was a large house at the corner of

02:20.760 --> 02:24.180
Blenham Street. Its owner, a rich, old

02:24.180 --> 02:28.400
woman, had died a few days ago. The University bought

02:28.400 --> 02:31.540
the house immediately. Now the house

02:31.540 --> 02:35.300
was empty. There was wood across the front door and

02:35.300 --> 02:38.980
the windows were broken. Someone looked

02:38.980 --> 02:42.140
out of a window. It was a man of about

02:42.140 --> 02:45.860
20. He had long hair and was wearing a headband.

02:46.740 --> 02:52.760
He looked strange. He was a squatter. Squatters live in

02:52.760 --> 02:55.120
old empty houses and they don't pay

02:55.120 --> 03:00.380
any rent. The stranger waved to Stuart. He wanted to

03:00.380 --> 03:11.800
speak to Stuart. What does he want? Stuart

03:12.540 --> 03:19.040
like to help me. Okay. Watch this house. How long?

03:19.800 --> 03:25.960
Half an hour. Okay. I'm Stuart. My name's Frank.

03:27.040 --> 03:30.240
I'll go and get my things. Are you going to

03:30.240 --> 03:34.320
squatter here, Frank? Yes. Don't let anyone else in.

03:35.120 --> 03:44.080
I'll be back soon. Okay. See you. Frank walked off

03:44.080 --> 03:46.860
slowly down the street. His head was

03:46.860 --> 03:49.480
bent forward and he was looking down at the pavement.

03:50.280 --> 03:52.820
He was about 20 but he looked much

03:52.820 --> 03:57.720
older. Frank went round the corner and Stuart turned towards

03:57.720 --> 04:00.060
the house. It looked interesting.

04:01.440 --> 04:05.840
The window was low, quite near the ground. The street

04:05.840 --> 04:09.100
was empty. Stuart put one leg over

04:09.100 --> 04:14.180
the window sill and looked inside. Outside the sun was

04:14.180 --> 04:17.680
shining brightly. Inside the house it was

04:17.680 --> 04:23.180
dark. Stuart stood for a few moments and waited. Slowly

04:23.180 --> 04:25.140
the inside of the room became clearer.

04:26.440 --> 04:29.840
There was a calendar on the wall. Lots of old

04:29.840 --> 04:31.820
newspapers were lying around on the floor.

04:33.200 --> 04:36.760
There was a mattress against the far wall. It looked

04:36.760 --> 04:40.600
new. Stuart looked up and down the street.

04:41.640 --> 04:45.400
There was no one around. He quickly climbed into the

04:45.400 --> 04:51.080
room. Stuart walked to the middle of the room

04:51.080 --> 04:55.120
and kicked away the old newspapers. There was nothing underneath

04:55.120 --> 04:57.000
them. There was no carpet

04:57.580 --> 05:02.340
and the floorboards were covered with dirt. Stuart took the

05:02.340 --> 05:03.600
calendar down from the wall.

05:04.500 --> 05:08.240
It was an old one, five years old. No one

05:08.240 --> 05:09.760
had changed it for five years.

05:10.920 --> 05:15.060
Then Stuart remembered. The owner of the house, the old

05:15.060 --> 05:17.200
woman, had been ill for a long time.

05:17.860 --> 05:20.640
She hadn't got out of her bed for five years.

05:22.920 --> 05:26.760
The mattress was leaning against the far wall. Stuart went

05:26.760 --> 05:28.200
over and looked at it carefully.

05:29.660 --> 05:33.760
It was a good mattress. Stuart picked up the mattress

05:33.760 --> 05:35.500
and turned it over carefully.

05:37.040 --> 05:41.220
There was some stitching along one side, about ten centimeters

05:41.220 --> 05:41.640
long.

05:42.780 --> 05:46.300
Stuart held the mattress between his knees and took out

05:46.300 --> 05:47.020
a small knife.

05:49.280 --> 05:52.780
Stuart cut the stitches carefully and then put his hand

05:52.780 --> 05:56.020
in the hole. He felt a bundle of newspapers

05:56.580 --> 06:05.120
and pulled it out. He quickly unwrapped it. Inside the

06:05.120 --> 06:07.940
bundle of newspapers there were some bank notes.

06:13.900 --> 06:20.920
Suddenly, Stuart heard a voice. It was Frank. Hey, Stuart,

06:21.780 --> 06:24.680
where are you? Frank was shouting.

06:25.860 --> 06:28.780
Stuart quickly wrapped up the money inside the newspapers.

06:31.900 --> 06:36.340
He held the bundle behind his back. I'm in here,

06:36.340 --> 06:38.120
Frank. He shouted.

06:39.560 --> 06:42.460
Frank came up to the window and looked into the

06:42.460 --> 06:42.620
room.

06:43.940 --> 06:46.780
What are you doing in there? Frank asked.

06:47.680 --> 06:51.380
Nothing! replied Stuart. I'm looking around.

06:52.860 --> 06:56.080
Frank climbed into the room and came closer to Stuart.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.400
Stuart moved to the wall. He held the bundle of

07:00.400 --> 07:01.720
newspapers behind his back.

07:03.240 --> 07:07.660
Frank looked around the room. He didn't see Stuart's knife

07:07.660 --> 07:08.240
on the floor.

07:09.780 --> 07:11.820
You haven't taken anything, have you?

07:12.260 --> 07:13.160
Asked Frank.

07:14.140 --> 07:17.580
I haven't taken anything of yours, replied Stuart.

07:18.860 --> 07:21.860
You've moved this mattress, said Frank.

07:23.160 --> 07:25.980
Frank picked up the mattress and turned it over carefully.

07:27.180 --> 07:29.260
Then he saw the hole in the side.

07:30.420 --> 07:36.760
You cut this mattress. It was stitched. Is this your

07:36.760 --> 07:37.100
knife?

07:37.880 --> 07:42.240
Yes. What were you doing? Nothing.

07:42.900 --> 07:48.840
You found something. I didn't. What's that in your hand?

07:49.980 --> 07:58.020
Where? Behind your back. Nothing. You got something. Some old

07:58.020 --> 07:58.700
newspapers.

07:59.780 --> 08:02.400
And them over. They're mine!

08:05.300 --> 08:08.720
Stuart remembered the motorbike. He needed the money.

08:09.540 --> 08:12.100
He was going to keep it. It was his money,

08:12.340 --> 08:13.220
not Frank's.

08:14.260 --> 08:18.200
Frank was holding Stuart's knife in his hand. He came

08:18.200 --> 08:18.940
nearer to Stuart.

08:20.100 --> 08:23.840
Give me those newspapers. He said again.

08:24.840 --> 08:26.140
Stuart had an idea.

08:27.420 --> 08:30.320
There's something else in the mattress, he said to Frank.

08:30.940 --> 08:34.080
There was something under the newspapers. It's still there.

08:35.580 --> 08:38.920
Frank looked at Stuart for a few moments. He didn't

08:38.920 --> 08:39.760
believe him at first.

08:40.880 --> 08:43.100
Look and see, said Stuart.

08:44.280 --> 08:47.400
Frank put the knife down on the floor. He picked

08:47.400 --> 08:50.100
up the mattress and put his hand deep in the

08:50.100 --> 08:50.320
hole.

08:51.560 --> 08:54.960
Stuart did not wait for a moment. He turned and

08:54.960 --> 08:57.000
jumped out through the window into the street.

08:59.080 --> 09:02.800
He ran quickly. There was a turning on the right.

09:03.780 --> 09:07.440
Stuart ran around the corner. He heard a shout behind

09:07.440 --> 09:09.140
him. It was Frank.

09:10.420 --> 09:15.220
Around the corner, there was another old empty house. It

09:15.220 --> 09:16.900
had a large garden on one side.

09:17.580 --> 09:22.160
Thick bushes had grown all over the garden. Stuart jumped

09:22.160 --> 09:23.220
over the low wall.

09:24.140 --> 09:26.980
He ran for a few meters and then hid under

09:26.980 --> 09:27.380
some bushes.

09:28.900 --> 09:33.940
Stuart heard more shouting and footsteps. The footsteps became louder

09:33.940 --> 09:35.660
than they stopped.

09:37.060 --> 09:42.620
Stuart waited silently. He did not breathe. Then the footsteps

09:42.620 --> 09:43.820
started once again.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.680
Stuart laughed quietly to himself.

09:51.140 --> 09:55.180
Frank had quickly picked up Stuart's knife. He jumped out

09:55.180 --> 09:56.320
of the window after him.

09:57.520 --> 10:00.320
Frank saw Stuart. He was running around the corner.

10:01.460 --> 10:04.900
Frank ran after him and turned the corner. But the

10:04.900 --> 10:05.640
street was empty.

10:06.900 --> 10:11.320
Frank stopped for a few moments and looked around. He

10:11.320 --> 10:12.320
noticed the old garden.

10:14.000 --> 10:19.300
Perhaps he's in there. Thought Frank. But everything in the

10:19.300 --> 10:20.100
garden was quiet.

10:21.200 --> 10:25.240
Frank saw nothing. There was another corner farther down the

10:25.240 --> 10:25.480
street.

10:26.760 --> 10:31.340
Frank started running again. He was still holding Stuart's knife.

10:33.220 --> 10:36.900
Stuart was happy. He had escaped from Frank with the

10:36.900 --> 10:37.100
money.

10:38.260 --> 10:41.340
Stuart sat up under the bushes and opened up the

10:41.340 --> 10:41.540
newspapers.

10:41.540 --> 10:45.080
The banknotes were wrapped tightly together.

10:46.560 --> 10:49.160
Stuart unwrapped them and counted them carefully.

10:50.540 --> 10:55.100
10, 20, 30.

10:59.940 --> 11:00.740
325.

11:02.020 --> 11:02.660
125.

11:06.720 --> 11:13.860
Stuart had found 325 pounds and Martin wanted 350 pounds

11:13.860 --> 11:14.720
for his motorbike.

11:16.500 --> 11:19.440
It was cool in the garden and Stuart lay back

11:19.440 --> 11:19.980
under the bushes.

11:21.880 --> 11:25.980
I'll wait here for half an hour, thought Stuart. Then

11:25.980 --> 11:26.840
I'll go to Martin.

11:30.580 --> 11:33.620
It was now nearly 12 o'clock. The day was

11:33.620 --> 11:34.340
getting much hotter.

11:35.400 --> 11:37.680
A police car was parked in a side street.

11:38.900 --> 11:42.720
There were two policemen in the car. The sergeant, a

11:42.720 --> 11:45.060
fat, round-faced man, was half asleep.

11:46.100 --> 11:49.200
The other policeman was younger and taller. He was a

11:49.200 --> 11:49.700
constable.

11:50.860 --> 11:55.900
Suddenly, the constable sat up. He had seen something strange.

11:56.980 --> 12:01.140
"'Wake up, Sergeant,' he shouted. Look over there!'

12:02.380 --> 12:07.240
"'Where? Look at what,' asked the sergeant, still half asleep.

12:07.840 --> 12:12.480
"'Over there! Someone's running with a knife,' replied the constable.

12:12.840 --> 12:15.600
"'The man's gone mad. It's this heat.'

12:16.280 --> 12:19.800
"'Wake! Get out and catch him,' said the sergeant.

12:21.480 --> 12:25.600
The two policemen jumped out of their car. Frank saw

12:25.600 --> 12:25.960
the policeman.

12:26.960 --> 12:30.760
He threw Stuart's knife away and started to run. The

12:30.760 --> 12:33.180
constable soon caught him and held his arm

12:33.180 --> 12:37.440
tightly. The sergeant found the knife in some long grass.

12:38.720 --> 12:40.630
The constable took Frank towards the

12:40.630 --> 12:44.290
police car. The sergeant came up to them. He was

12:44.290 --> 12:44.970
holding the knife.

12:46.950 --> 12:50.490
"'Oh, it's you,' the sergeant said to Frank.

12:52.510 --> 12:57.510
"'What's going on, Frank? I'm looking for a guy. With

12:57.510 --> 13:02.050
a knife? What guy? He stole in my money.

13:02.050 --> 13:08.530
What money? How much money? I don't know. A lot.

13:09.370 --> 13:10.450
He don't know.

13:11.490 --> 13:17.250
Where did you get it? In an old house. Come

13:17.250 --> 13:18.770
on into the car."

13:28.990 --> 13:33.250
"'Where are you taking me?' asked Frank. To the police

13:33.250 --> 13:35.410
station,' replied the constable.

13:35.930 --> 13:39.690
"'But I haven't done anything. The money was mine. That

13:39.690 --> 13:41.930
guy took it. But what's his name?

13:41.930 --> 13:47.610
Stuart. Stuart took it. "'Who's Stuart?' asked the constable.

13:48.190 --> 13:52.310
"'I met him in an old house,' replied Frank. "'Where

13:52.310 --> 13:54.510
you found the money?' asked the sergeant.

13:55.470 --> 14:00.330
"'Yes,' I found it inside a mattress,' said Frank. "'Who's

14:00.330 --> 14:01.130
got the money now?'

14:01.650 --> 14:05.970
asked the sergeant. "'That guy, Stuart,' he ran away with

14:05.970 --> 14:06.090
it.

14:07.090 --> 14:10.730
"'So now we have to find Stuart,' said the constable.

14:16.870 --> 14:20.590
Stuart waited in the garden for half an hour. It

14:20.590 --> 14:23.470
was getting hotter. It was nearly 12 o'clock.

14:24.810 --> 14:29.370
"'I'll have to move now,' thought Stuart. Martin goes for

14:29.370 --> 14:30.550
his lunch at half past 12.

14:32.210 --> 14:36.150
Stuart looked out carefully from the bushes. The garden was

14:36.150 --> 14:36.470
empty.

14:37.650 --> 14:40.850
He hurried out of the garden onto the street. He

14:40.850 --> 14:42.130
walked towards Martin's garage.

14:43.390 --> 14:47.490
Stuart did not see the police car. It stopped outside

14:47.490 --> 14:49.210
the garden a few moments later.

14:50.350 --> 14:54.670
"'Look in this garden,' Frank told the policeman. Perhaps he's

14:54.670 --> 14:55.410
hiding in here.

15:02.350 --> 15:07.970
"'Hi, Martin. Hi, Stuart. How much for the bike?'

15:08.370 --> 15:17.210
£350. I want it. How much for me? Still £350.

15:18.270 --> 15:24.170
Have you any money? Yes. How much? £300.

15:24.170 --> 15:28.230
£300. That's not enough. £325?

15:31.270 --> 15:35.050
Okay. She's yours. Great. Thanks.

15:40.950 --> 15:44.830
The policeman got out of the car. Frank got out,

15:44.970 --> 15:48.070
too. The constable held his arm tightly.

15:48.990 --> 15:52.790
The sergeant went into the garden. He looked around for

15:52.790 --> 15:54.990
some time. Then he came back.

15:55.890 --> 15:57.490
He was holding a bundle of newspapers.

15:59.310 --> 16:02.910
"'There's no one there,' the sergeant said, that I found

16:02.910 --> 16:03.910
these old newspapers.

16:05.230 --> 16:09.590
"'That's them,' shouted Frank. Something was wrapped in those newspapers.'

16:09.590 --> 16:13.910
Just then a motorbike drove up towards the police car.

16:14.710 --> 16:20.250
"'That's him,' shouted Frank excitedly. That's the guy. He's bought

16:20.250 --> 16:21.710
a motorbike with my money.

16:23.650 --> 16:29.090
"'Stop,' the sergeant called to Stuart. Stop.'

16:30.950 --> 16:35.930
Stuart did not see Frank. What do the police want?'

16:35.930 --> 16:37.030
Stuart asked himself.

16:37.770 --> 16:41.350
"'I haven't done anything wrong. I'm driving correctly.'

16:42.610 --> 16:45.130
Stuart stopped the bike by the side of the road.

16:45.730 --> 16:46.910
He took off his helmet.

16:48.190 --> 16:51.350
"'Is that bike yours?' the sergeant asked him.

16:51.950 --> 16:56.410
"'Yes, it's mine,' replied Stuart. I'd bought it at the

16:56.410 --> 16:57.450
garage down the road.'

16:58.450 --> 17:00.110
Then Stuart saw Frank.

17:01.270 --> 17:05.410
"'What have you told these cops?' Stuart shouted angrily at

17:05.410 --> 17:05.650
Frank.

17:07.430 --> 17:12.870
"'We'll all go to this garage,' said the sergeant. They

17:12.870 --> 17:14.630
all walked back to Martin's garage.

17:19.130 --> 17:23.330
"'A big black cloud now covered the sun. It was

17:23.330 --> 17:24.050
beginning to rain.

17:25.510 --> 17:31.210
"'So this loud fades you 325 pounds for this bike,'

17:31.210 --> 17:34.170
the sergeant said to Martin. Martin agreed.

17:35.190 --> 17:38.490
"'And where did you get this money?' the sergeant asked

17:38.490 --> 17:38.790
Stuart.

17:39.750 --> 17:43.210
"'I found it,' replied Stuart. I found it in a

17:43.210 --> 17:46.030
mattress. It was in an empty house.'

17:46.770 --> 17:48.770
The sergeant took the money from Martin.

17:50.090 --> 17:53.650
"'We'll look after this money,' he said. You two can

17:53.650 --> 17:54.130
go now.

17:55.010 --> 17:59.510
"'It's my money,' shouted Frank. "'Do you want to come

17:59.510 --> 18:01.530
to the police station with us?'

18:01.530 --> 18:02.970
asked the constable.

18:04.310 --> 18:06.510
Frank walked away, still shouting.

18:08.250 --> 18:11.170
"'I'm sorry,' Martin said to Stuart.

18:11.570 --> 18:13.230
"'It's my bike again.'

18:13.690 --> 18:16.070
"'Not for long,' replied Stuart.

18:17.210 --> 18:19.850
"'What do you mean?' asked the sergeant.

18:21.350 --> 18:24.570
"'It has started to rain now,' replied Stuart.

18:25.370 --> 18:28.570
"'I don't want a holiday. I'm going to get a

18:28.570 --> 18:28.890
job.

18:29.550 --> 18:34.330
"'I'm going to save another 325 pounds and buy that

18:34.330 --> 18:35.210
bike.'

18:56.970 --> 19:01.570
"'Money for a Motorbike was read by William Gaminara and

19:01.570 --> 19:06.570
the recording produced by James Richardson at Studio AVP London.'

